In a press briefing, White House Press Secretary Sarah Sanders addressed the recent terrorist attack in New York City and called for immigration reforms to enhance national security. She also emphasized the need to destroy the ideology behind ISIS. Sanders also fielded questions regarding accusations of sexual misconduct against President Trump and stated that the President denies the allegations. She further discussed the President's stance on tax reform, the special Senate election in Alabama, and the President's upcoming announcement on space policy. Sanders also mentioned that the suspect in the New York attack came to the United States through chain migration, highlighting the need for immigration reform.